 Lagos State Governor, Mr Babajide Sanwo-Olu on Thursday appointed a former Head of Service in the state, Mrs. Folasade Jaji, as the new Secretary to the State Government. This was disclosed in a statement issued by the Head of Service, Mr. Hakeem Muri-Okunola, in Lagos. Jaji, a chemist, had served as the 17th Head of Service of the state’s Public Service. She joined the Lagos State Civil Service on October 27, 1980 at the State Judicial Service Commission before she was deployed to the Governor’s Office, Department of Political Affairs where she served for two years between 1980 and 1982. She is the 18th Secretary to the State Government. The statement said that full details about the appointment would come later. 